skov\\\", 27, true);\\n\\n            Iterable<Person> saved = repository.saveAll(Arrays.asList(ada, grace, alan, barbara));\\n            assertThat(idsOf(saved)).containsExactly(\\\"p1\\\", \\\"p2\\\", \\\"p3\\\", \\\"p4\\\");\\n\\n[151 more lines in file. Use offset=261 to continue.]\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778265933907}}\n/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge8/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/logs/org.springframework.data:spring-data-keyvalue:2.7.18/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-08T18-45-53-623806Z.log:1668:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Verifying line lengths**\\n\\nI need to ensure that I'm checking the line lengths for checkstyle. It’s important to understand the guidelines around this to avoid any formatting issues later. I want to be thorough since readability is key in coding standards. Let’s read through the relevant section to confirm what the exact requirements are. Getting this right will help maintain consistency in the code, which is always a good practice!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_024744fb1e26de0a0169fe2f4ac61881a0b6fa751cef358b43\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp_i9N_UuO2igIMTF7-k_M_G2n-vOPqVx5lKaZtdYU8w2ICzdo1VFypFEX4oCOafao0gXDqpiFyC-AQYsF97vgFPydd7PnDGgU_lbH4g8ar18fLrbdVw7nIzml--BxRtWHsaWhofuIK-cctipVczjHLALdhTRCI_DRwDF20afrITS173fCooNQK23m-7KBcbAuZDb-Yh6vtrpRLs5dT4Xo3LmjsW_zv-v0TpmXQjAtqfcMTO7iQWP60f6FT3M05joq5lCUyYCQt92lRehn6KsJU3MSbOxbNXa70m9pXpJknZiA5Gz8XnVDGCDDirl8AMdIVd3PA-W23_MD4MplIhGEahZNnB_4sIBMY-KmPpAB1HpvC5BpzXnsO_tzdygAnryGFyU4pNLE6rOCK8sokq6M_5flWKh3blPI4ArrXlD2XMy2WmL_3YfEhiBjPOpvpf5XQt0afRMMRH5WpSUwr8Cny6mzWIWc-Wc5O1mxXEtf7vehFDAuynzT3RmKFtk8mrFWYGkDoy-7B735pXmD66LAJgoYnxPfts5KVfgpKdzMSsCGw1MS8O_3AjLcnkbqlQXnjYuJPIGz_W0erfXWo63pOwsfBXixcI3a_u9xGZkXnTCwzlW1zXqWMno7u0ynBtAzeSmW1cB38JRyXBkYiX6ii4Vnbx-3W8p8t56jfM1K0nun20h6DSp_SUn1GTPI5bxaEOuuYrrnoI-c6